# Grid

As a rule, we use flexbox for responsive grids.
If there is a compelling reason to use something else,
feel free to do so, but don't use Bootstrap merely because you know it.

The examples below are just representative of the frequently occurring flex patterns we use.

Flexbox has dozens, if not hundreds of other combinations that are useful in a variety of situations,
so don't be reliant on these few classes.

If you are new to flexbox, this is a fun game to get started: [flexboxfroggy.com](http://flexboxfroggy.com/)


## Flex Row

### Default

```
<div class='flex-row border-dashed-darkgray'>
 <div class='border-darkgray flex-example'>
    Element One
 </div>
 <div class='border-darkgray flex-example'>
    Element Two
 </div>
 <div class='border-darkgray flex-example'>
    Element Three
 </div>
</div>
@css {
    .flex-example {
        min-width: 225px;
        text-align: center;
    }
}
```

